    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="60"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 60 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HK1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-14">14 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and top secret for the President from <persName corresp="#p_HK1"
                        >Harriman</persName>.</p>
                <p>I am wondering whether there is anything you wish me to take up with <persName
                        corresp="#p_SMIV2">Marshal Stalin</persName> in regard to the arrangements
                    for your forthcoming meeting. I had assumed that <persName corresp="#p_EGADD1"
                        >General Eisenhower</persName> would be instructed to work out the
                    arrangements in Berlin with <persName corresp="#p_ZMGK1">Marshal
                        Zhukov</persName>, on the other hand there will undoubtedly be some matters
                    which will have to be discussed in Moscow in order that appropriate instructions
                    may be sent <persName corresp="#p_ZMGK1">Zhukov</persName>.</p>
                <p>From my experience with the last two meetings,<note n="1" xml:id="d60fn1">i. e.,
                        the conferences at Tehran and Yalta.</note> the Russians will probably be
                    asking me shortly for information as to your plans. They will also wish to know
                    who[m] you intend to bring so that they may select the members of their
                    party[.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
